Pork and Crab or Shrimp Pastry Rolls

1/2 Lb. lean ground Pork
1/4 C. Flaked Crabmeat or minced cooked shrimp
1/4 C. Minced water Chestnuts
2 Tbsp. Minced Scallions
2 Tbsp. Bread crumbs
1 Tbsp. Soy Sauce
1 tsp. Minced Gingerroot
1 Egg beaten
1/2 tsp minced Garlic
1/4 tsp. Salt
1/4 tsp. Asian Sesame Oil
Cream Cheese pastry (you can use the freezerpuff pastry also)

Sauté Pork till looses color but do not Brown.

Add crab meat or shrimp, chestnuts, scallions, bread crumbs, soy,
gingerroot, egg, garlic, salt, and sesame oil.

If too runny add more bread crumbs. Use to fill turnovers, logs or
rissoles.

Can be prepared 2 days in advance.

Makes: 36 Pastries
-----------------------------

Cream Cheese Pastry

This dough can be made up to 4 days in advance.

1 C. Butter
2 1/2 C. Flour
1 C. Cream Cheese
1 tsp. Salt
1/4 C. Heavy Cream

Cream the butter and the cream cheese. Gradually beat in cream. Add in
flour and salt and blend well. Wrap and chill for an hour before using.

50 pastries

